## Summary

`SwipeItemView` subscribes to `Command.CanExecuteChanged` with a **plain (non-weak) delegate** and only unsubscribes when the `Command` property itself changes. When a `SwipeItemView` is bound to an `ICommand` owned by a longer-lived source (a singleton/static view-model, an app-level command, etc.) and the view is then detached/navigated-away **without** the `Command` being cleared, the command's invocation list keeps the `SwipeItemView` (and its whole visual subtree) alive forever.

This is the same class of leak already hardened elsewhere in MAUI via `WeakCommandSubscription` (`src/Controls/src/Core/WeakCommandSubscription.cs`), but `SwipeItemView` still uses the raw subscription.

## Retention path

`ICommand (long-lived) -> CanExecuteChanged delegate -> SwipeItemView.OnCommandCanExecuteChanged -> SwipeItemView -> visual subtree`

Citations (repo `src/Controls/src/Core/SwipeView/SwipeItemView.cs`):
- Line 62 — `Command.CanExecuteChanged += OnCommandCanExecuteChanged;` (strong subscribe in `OnCommandChanged`)
- Lines 65–71 — `OnCommandChanging` only unsubscribes when the `Command` value changes; there is no unload/teardown hook, so navigating away never removes the handler.

## Observed results

| Scenario | Alive (of 30) | Retained |
|----------|--------------:|---------:|
| Control (no Command assigned) | 0 | ~0 MB |
| Mitigation (Command set to null before discard) | 0 | ~0 MB |
| **Leaky (Command left assigned, view detached)** | **30** | **~30 MB** |

## Affected platforms

Purely managed cross-platform code (`src/Controls/src/Core`) → **all platforms**.

## Suggested fix

Route the `CanExecuteChanged` subscription through `WeakCommandSubscription` (as `Button`/`MenuItem`/`RefreshView` already do), or unsubscribe from the command on handler-disconnect / unload.

**Scope note:** Clear framework-hardenable issue. A shared/long-lived `ICommand` is a completely ordinary MVVM pattern, and the user has no unload hook to null the `Command`, so the framework should use a weak subscription here.

