# .NET MAUI Workaround: Uniform Line Heights for FormattedText

If you use `FormattedText` in .NET MAUI with a custom `LineHeight`, you've likely noticed that mixing different fonts or sizes within spans destroys the uniform vertical line spacing of the label. On Android, the line height becomes wildly inconsistent per-line, and certain fonts (like those with large native leading) inflate the spacing excessively.

Below is a complete, drop-in workaround that you can add to your MAUI app to force mathematically perfect, uniform line heights across both iOS and Android.

## How to use it

You can apply this workaround globally by appending our custom handler to the `LabelHandler.Mapper` during your app's initialization (for example, in your `App.xaml.cs` constructor or `MauiProgram.cs`).

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();

    // Register the custom uniform line height handler
    Microsoft.Maui.Handlers.LabelHandler.Mapper.AppendToMapping(nameof(Label.FormattedText), UniformLineHeightHandler);
    Microsoft.Maui.Handlers.LabelHandler.Mapper.AppendToMapping(nameof(Label.LineHeight), UniformLineHeightHandler);
}
```

## The Complete Handler Code

